modules.description: This module enables bidirectional conversion between enumerated types (e.g., CID versions, IPLD formats, cryptographic keys) and integer codes, along with mappings to string representations for identifiers like multihash, multiaddr, and protocol-specific types. It operates on data structures used in decentralized systems, such as cryptographic primitives, network protocols, and serialized identifiers, primarily serving use cases in IPFS and Filecoin for encoding, decoding, and interoperable data exchange.
